		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hinges have been a main point of failure for most of the laptops I've owned.<br /><br />On one where I had the hinge seize up like that, I ended up just removing it and let the laptop live out the rest of its life with only one working hinge. Was a bit floppier after that. At other times I've sent a laptop back for repair (various amounts of success, might be without the machine for a while and they might only do very minimal repair without addressing the root cause), but most of the time I'll just do something hacky to it myself so I don't have to wait, but I tend to treat mine very roughly as well.

		

		</td>
